  "texts": [
    "It provides vital funding for large research institutes such as BAIR and Stanford's HAI, yet it also offers access to the next generation of industry recruits.",
    "This concurs with the call for a \"voice of reason\" by various interviewees.",
    "A lot of academic stakeholders have pushed to establish a future imaginary around \"AI as a tool\" rather than a \"key technology\", which colours AI development as utopian instead of setting realistic expectations for tech literacy and political safeguarding.",
    "This dichotomy between securing private funding for critical and relevant non-commercial work, while remaining a crucial voice in public AI discourse, is further reflected in the third connected sector: advocacy organisations are closely tied to industry actors in the U.S., with various interviewees having repeatedly moved between academia, industry and advocacy.",
    "This creates an interesting trifecta of deeply connected sectors."
